snippet.title: Boulder Dash - [Arcade, Data East] Failed longplay (1990)
snippet.description:
A miserable attempt to coin feed through Data East's Boulder Dash (1990)... you actually need gameplay skills to play this game ;)
The main reason i recorded it was to make a reference for emulator programmers to use when trying emulating the game. I managed to play to map 5-2 and gave up after playing the level for about 20 minutes :/
This video was uploaded almost 3 years ago exactly today but i have kept the video private listed since it was a bit embarrassing not to be able to coin feed through it :)
The sound and video is not syncing perfectly though because of my recording setup.

*****
Recorded from the original arcade PCB using Micomsoft RGB capturecard SC-500N1 and Xsync-1, software used is AmarecTV and Virtualdub.
*****
